Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Gus Atkinson draws first blood for England and Dimuth Karunaratne is a goner! A short ball out of nowhere by Atkinson, dug in over off stump and just angling across, Karunaratne's eyes light up as he looks to take it on but gets rushed and a feather of an outside edge is found. The ball goes through quickly to the keeper and Jamie Smith makes no mistake. A bit more of an edge and that would have flown over the keeper and the slip cordon, Sri Lanka 6/1!
Default_Commentary: 5.3: Gus Atkinson to Dimuth Karunaratne, OUT! c Jamie Smith b Gus Atkinson.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Oh, dear! A moment that Nishan Madushka will be thinking about on his way back but for now, England have got rid of both the Lankan openers and pretty cheaply as well. Chris Woakes dishes out a full and wide ball, swinging it away as well, Madushka extends his arms and looks for the expansive drive but doesn't quite get to the pitch of the ball and the outside edge is found. The ball travels quickly to first slip where Joe Root pouches it around his stomach and Sri Lanka in early trouble here.

Howout: c Joe Root b Chris Woakes

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Oh, wow! Angelo Mathews has just shouldered arms at a delivery that jagged back in a long way and gets pinged on the pads. A huge appeal and up goes the finger but Mathews does review it. The only thing that can save him here is height as it looked pretty straight. Chris Woakes bowls this one on a fullish length and wide of the off stump, Mathews sees the line and looks to leave it alone but it is the big inswinger and the ball just jags back in sharply. The ball crashes into the pads, and Ball Tracking comes up with three reds. Mathews has to walk back and it will be a double-wicket maiden for Woakes.

Howout: lbw b Chris Woakes

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Oh dear that one stayed pretty low and there was not much Chandimal could do about it. A huge shout for LBW and the umpire raises his finger! Dinesh Chandimal has a chat with his partner and opts for a review at the very last second. Shoaib Bashir comes from over the wicket and bowls much fuller on off. Dinesh Chandimal hangs back and looks to tuck it on the leg side but the ball stays very low and scoots under his bat to thump his back pad. The replays roll back on and the UltraEdge shows no bat involvement and the Ball Tracking turns up to be three reds. Sri Lanka now lose half their side and are in all sorts of trouble at 72/5!
Default_Commentary: 22.3: Shoaib Bashir to Dinesh Chandimal, OUT! lbw b Shoaib Bashir.
Howout: lbw b Shoaib Bashir

Commentary: Oh dear! Just when it felt like Gus Atkinson had provided another crucial breakthrough and his string of short balls had done the trick for England, the umpire rechecks for the height and deems it a No-ball! Atkinson bangs it short and over off, Prabath Jayasuriya plays a nothing shot off it away from his body and just chips it in the air towards gully where Root settles and takes a simple catch. Jayasuriya survives a scare and walks back in to bat as a dejected Gus Atkinson trudges back to bowl the next one!
Default_Commentary: 33.5: Gus Atkinson to Prabath Jayasuriya, No ball!

Commentary: On a short of a length and over the stumps, Prabath Jayasuriya makes room and looks for the big slog straight over the bowler's head but misses.
Default_Commentary: 33.5: Gus Atkinson to Prabath Jayasuriya, No run.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Exceptional bowling from Gus Atkinson, who doesn't need any assistance from the umpire on this as he sends Prabath Jayasuriya walking back for the second time. A well-deserved wicket! Bowls it fuller this time and surprises Jayasuriya who wasn't expecting the length to be full. Lands it just outside off and Prabath Jayasuriya just looks to fend it out away from his body. Gets an outside edge straight to the keeper Jamie Smith who collects it well to his right. Sri Lanka slip further down and are now 113/7!
Default_Commentary: 33.6: Gus Atkinson to Prabath Jayasuriya, OUT! c Jamie Smith b Gus Atkinson.
Howout: c Jamie Smith b Gus Atkinson

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Persistence pays off for England as they finally break through and claim the wicket they were after! Milan Rathnayake's gritty knock of 72 runs comes to an end, and he walks off to a standing ovation from his teammates and the crowd. Bashir loops it full and on middle and leg, Milan Rathnayake looked for the big swing over mid on but mistimes this one. Hits it off the cue end and straight to Chris Woakes at mid on. Sri Lanka are now 226/9!

Commentary: OUT! RUN OUT! A mixup against the run of play and Sri Lanka get bundled out for 236 runs. Joe Root bowls it nice and full on the stumps, Vishwa Fernando tucks it in front of Ollie Pope at mid-wicket before setting off for a quick single. Asitha Fernando sends him back, leaving Vishwa stranded halfway down the track. Pope quickly collects the ball and throws it to keeper Jamie Smith, who swiftly knocks the bails off. Despite a desperate dive from Vishwa Fernando, he was well short of the crease, bringing Sri Lanka's innings to a close.
Default_Commentary: 73.6: Joe Root to Vishwa Fernando, OUT! run out (Ollie Pope / Jamie Smith).
Howout: run out (Ollie Pope / Jamie Smith)

Dan Lawrence though thinks he has been hit high on the pads and this could be missing the stumps. He has a chat with his partner and takes the review. Looking at the delivery, it is a good-length ball that jags back in sharply from outside off. Dan Lawrence takes a blow on his knee roll here, with some extra bounce. The third umpire has a closer look and confirms that the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the stumps. Dan Lawrence survives here.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Asitha Fernando could not send Dan Lawrence two deliveries prior, but this time he gets rid of the big fish in Ben Duckett. Asitha Fernando and Sri Lanka are pumped up here and why not, they needed an early wicket and they have got one. Brilliant bowling from Fernando. He goes a bit fuller this time, around middle and gets it to jag back into the left-hander. Ben Duckett is caught inside the crease. He tries to flick it away but misses. Dhananjaya de Silva took the review after a word with his bowler, and it worked out pretty well for the visitors, as the Ball Tracking showed three reds.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND!  A crucial wicket against the run of play, providing much-needed relief for Sri Lanka. Milan Rathnayake claims his first Test wicket, and while it wasn’t his finest delivery, it still does the job for the visitors, securing a valuable breakthrough. He bowls it on a good length but down leg, Gus Atkinson covers the line and looks to flick but only manages to get a feather off the inside edge. Dinesh Chandimal does very well to dive to his left and take a sharp low catch. The UltraEdge reconfirms the spike and the third umpire is satisfied with the clean catch as well. England now 305/7 and lead by 69 runs.
Default_Commentary: 76.5: Milan Rathnayake to Gus Atkinson, OUT! c Dinesh Chandimal b Milan Rathnayake.
Howout: c Dinesh Chandimal b Milan Rathnayake

Commentary: Huge appeal from the English players for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Chris Woakes discusses with Pope and he decides to opt for a review! Chris Woakes bowls a good-length delivery on middle, angling it away but shapes it back in on the middle. Dimuth Karunaratne hangs back and looks to push it away but gets squared up and the ball attacks the middle and it thumps his upper pad. The review shows that there's no bat involved in UltraEdge and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball misses the top of the middle stump because of the bounce. The decision remains the same and England lose a review!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Mark Wood comes in and breaks the partnership! What an impactful change this has been for England! Wood steams in from around the wicket to the left-hander and hits the deck hard, on a shorter length and angles it into the batter over middle and leg. Dimuth Karunaratne is stuck deep in the crease and cramped for room as he hops back and looks to tuck it away on the leg side. The ball catches the inside edge, goes off his thigh pads and lobs straight up in front of Harry Brook at second slip who takes the simplest of catches. A huge appeal goes around and the umpire after a long thought gives it out. Dimuth Karunaratne consults with Angelo Mathews to send it upstairs but decides against it and walks back.  Dinesh Chandimal is the new batter in.
Default_Commentary: 13.1: Mark Wood to Dimuth Karunaratne, OUT! c Harry Brook b Mark Wood.

Commentary: An appeal for lbw but turned down. This is an arm ball, full and around leg. Kamindu Mendis tries to flick it away but misses. The ball sneaks through and brushes his pads before Jamie Smith collects and whips the bails off. Ollie Pope has a long chat with the bowler and the wicket-keeper, Jamie Smith. He eventually decides to take it upstairs. To the naked eye, it looked as if it was going down leg. The replays roll back on and the third umpire confirms that Jamie Smith's gloves were not wholly behind the stumps as the ball was released and deems it a No Ball. England however, don't lose the review!

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! England gets the important breakthrough! Chris Woakes comes from over the stump and bowls it fuller on off and middle. Angelo Mathews looks to work it across the line but plays it a bit early. He gets the connection on the leading edge and the ball loops towards the front of the point fiedler. Matthew Potts dives to his front and gets the catch safe into his hands. Angelo Mathews has to depart after an exceptional knock!

Commentary: A huge shout for LBW and the umpire raises the finger with absolutely no hesitation. Milan Rathnayake sends it upstairs for a review. The UltraEdge shows a spike and Rathnayake survives an early scare. Top review this!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Oh dear, just jinxed it! Gus Atkinson finally breaks through and gets the biggest fish out in Kamindu Mendis! That dejected face of Chandimal says it all. Atkinson switches to 'round the wicket angle and lands it on a short of a length on off. Gets the ball to straighten a bit off the deck. Kamindu Mendis plays for the angle as he looks to punch it through the off side. Pokes at the delivery half-heartedly and ends up getting an outside edge to first slip. Joe Root crouches low and takes a sharp catch. Mendis walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd and the teammates on the balcony. He goes for a well-made 113.
Default_Commentary: 85.2: Gus Atkinson to Kamindu Mendis, OUT! c Joe Root b Gus Atkinson.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT by Harry Brook! He fumbles on the first attempt but secures it on the second. A crucial breakthrough for Potts. He bowls this outside off, on a nagging length tempting Jayasuriya to go for the drive. He does play it away from his body with not much foot movement and only manages to get a thick outside edge that flies straight to Harry Brook at second slip. He tries to take it high on the left but gets his fingers at it as the ball pops out behind him. He swivels quickly and grabs hold of it the second time.  Sri Lanka lose their 8th wicket with a lead of 199 runs.

Commentary: Survives the first one! Woakes hurls this fuller in length and gets the ball to shape away, from outside off, Vishwa Fernando gets closer to the line and leaves it alone.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Fernando doesn't survive the second one! Dinesh Chandimal suggests sending this upstairs and Fernando does. Woakes lands this full and on middle and leg, getting the ball to nip back in and skid through the surface. Vishwa Fernando opens his stance up and looks to keep it out but the ball zips past the bat to ping him on the pad. The UltraEdge shows no spike when the ball passes the bat and all three reds come up on the Ball Tracking. The on-field call stays and Vishwa Fernando walks back for a duck. Sri Lanka lose their 9th!
Default_Commentary: 88.6: Chris Woakes to Vishwa Fernando, OUT! lbw b Chris Woakes.
Howout: lbw b Chris Woakes

Commentary: FOUR! Nicely hit! Chandimal may just opt to go all out now. Fuller in length from Potts, on off, Dinesh Chandimal tonks it over mid off for a boundary.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Matthew Potts claims his third wicket as England finally manage to bowl Sri Lanka out for 326 runs. Chandimal, who could have stayed longer at the crease, opts to go big but ends up throwing his wicket away. Matthew Potts hurls this nice and full, in and around off, Dinesh Chandimal looks for the big heave through the off but doesn't quite get the timing right. Hits it high in the air over covers. Harry Singh the substitute fielder charges in from the ropes and settles under it to take a simple catch. Sri Lanka end with 204 run lead at the end of the innings.
Default_Commentary: 89.3: Matthew Potts to Dinesh Chandimal, OUT! c sub Harry Singh b Matthew Potts.
Howout: c sub Harry Singh b Matthew Potts

The replays roll back on, and the UltraEdge shows some spike as the ball goes past the edge of the bat. Joe Root survives and Sri Lanka lose a review. Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Big wicket for Sri Lanka! They have been provided with a much-needed breakthrough by Prabath Jayasuriya. Jayasuriya bowls it flatter and fuller just outside off, drifting it in. Harry Brook strides out and looks to push it past the bowler but he gets the connection from the inner edge. It goes uppishly to the left of the bowler. Prabath Jayasuriya stays low and picks the catch near his shoelaces to give his team an opening. England lose their fourth wicket in the form of Harry Brook. They are now 119/4, requiring 86 more runs to win.
Default_Commentary: 34.6: Prabath Jayasuriya to Harry Brook, OUT! c & b Prabath Jayasuriya.

Commentary: A big, big shout for LBW but turned down by the umpire! The around-the-wicket angle seemed to be taking the ball down leg. Slanting in, on a nagging length, on middle and leg, Joe Root walks across his stumps and takes a few steps ahead to clip it away but gets beaten on the inside edge to get rapped on the front pad. Dhananjaya de Silva sends it upstairs for a review. UltraEdge shows no bat but the Ball Tracking shows the wickets to be hitting but the impact is umpire's call since Root was more than 3 metres out of his crease. Sri Lanka keep their review but the on-field decision is upheld.
